      • copyTo

        public void copyTo(byte[] dest,
                   int destPos)
        Description copied from interface: Data
        Copies the payload contained in the Data to the destination buffer. The dest byte-buffer needs to be large enough to contain the payload. Otherwise an exception is thrown. The reason this method exists instead of relying on the Data.toByteArray() is the existence of the NativeMemoryData. With the NativeMemoryData it would lead to a temporary byte-array. This method prevents this temporary byte-array needing to be created.
        Specified by:
        copyTo in interface Data
        Parameters:
        dest - to byte-buffer to write to
        destPos - the position in the destination buffer.

      • getPartitionHash

        public int getPartitionHash()
        Description copied from interface: Data
        Returns partition hash calculated for serialized object. Partition hash is used to determine partition of a Data and is calculated using PartitioningStrategy during serialization.

        If partition hash is not set then standard hashCode() is used.

        Specified by:
        getPartitionHash in interface Data
        Returns:
        partition hash
        See Also:
        PartitionAware, PartitioningStrategy, SerializationService.toData(Object, com.hazelcast.core.PartitioningStrategy)
